      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of July 21 electoral college map that accompanied front-page article about presidential campaign</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An electoral college map on July 21 with a front-page article about the presidential campaign misstated Nebraska's method of allocating electoral votes. Like Maine, Nebraska awards one elector for the winner in each Congressional district and two for the statewide winner. It does not use the winner-take-all system followed by all other states and the District of Columbia.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
